RM  11967075
RT  The roles of the polytopic membrane proteins NarK, NarU and NirC in
RT  Escherichia coli K-12: two nitrate and three nitrite transporters.
RA  Clegg S; Yu F; Griffiths L; Cole JA;
RL  Mol Microbiol. 2002 Apr;44(1):143-55.
CC  Two polytopic membrane proteins of the major facilitator family, NarK and
CC  NarU, catalyse nitrate uptake into the Escherichia coli cytoplasm [1]. Both
CC  proteins also catalyse nitrite extrusion and nitrite uptake. A third
CC  protein, NirC, catalyses nitrite uptake, but it is unknown whether NirC
CC  also facilitates nitrite export
